            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_162gc' title='Col. 162GC &mdash; HL Deb 03 April 2003 vol 646 c162GC' name='column_162gc' href='#column_162gc' rel='bookmark'>162GC</a>
            statutory licensing system that involves a time-limited licence and a presumption for renewal which&#x2014;as the amendment proposes&#x2014;is written into primary legislation. If noble Lords have such an example, I shall consider it. My current legal advice, however, is that there is no such presumption in the terms of this amendment.
          </p>
