            In those circumstances, there would be no reasonable intervention by the Environment Agency. We are talking here about all abstractions of water&#x2014; all abstraction licences. There must be a right to intervene for unnecessary non-use of a licence that causes damage or uncertainty in the management of that water. That is all that does. The change is to reduce the period from seven to four years.
