            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_195gc' title='Col. 195GC &mdash; HL Deb 03 April 2003 vol 646 c195GC' name='column_195gc' href='#column_195gc' rel='bookmark'>195GC</a>
            by the reference to the agriculture sector. It would be difficult to specify one industry, important though it may be in the context, as needing representation before others.</p><p>
            The noble Lord, Lord Dixon-Smith, will recall that, sometimes, I have succumbed to rural arguments and, other times, I have not. For the moment, at least, I object to any addition to the list and am not prepared to look favourably on the amendments.
